## Install Latest Version of Package
THe follwoing block of code can be used to download and install the latest version of the MSTest R package from its github repository (https://github.com/roga11/MSTest). Installing packages directly from github requires using \textit{devtools}. The code below will check if devtools is already installed and install it if it is not.  
  
The package does not need to be re-installed every time. Just when new updates are avaiable. If you already have the latest version installed, you may proceed to the next section.
```{r}
rm(list=ls())
if (is.element('devtools',installed.packages()[,1])==FALSE){
  install.packages('devtools')
}
devtools::install_github('roga11/MSTest')
```
## Load Package

Once package has been installed it can be loaded. 
```{r}
library(MSTest)
```
## Load Data

The package includes 3 datasets that can be used as examples. The three datasets are:  
  
* hamilton84GNP: Data from 1951Q2 - 1984Q4 used in Hamilton (1989) and Hansen (1992; 1996)
* carhuplo10GNP: Data from 1951Q2 - 2010Q4 used by Carrasco, Hu and Ploberger (2014)
* kasshi14GDP: Data from 1960Q1 - 2014Q4 used in Kasahara and Shimotsu (2019)
  
They can be loaded using the following code. 
```{r}
GNPdata <- hamilton84GNP # this can be hamilton82GNP, carhuplo10GNP or kasshi18GNP
Y       <- GNPdata$GNP_logdiff
date    <- GNPdata$DATE 
plot(as.Date(date),Y,xlab='Time',ylab='GNP - log difference',type = 'l')
```
You an also learn more about these dataset and their sources by using the following line(s) and .
```{r}
?hamilton84GNP
```
## Simulated Data
```{r}
n = 500
mu = c(0,2)
std = c(1,2.5)
p = 0.9
q = 0.5
phi = c(0.5,0.25)
th = c(mu,p,q,std,phi)
Y_simu = simu_ARMS_dgp(n,th)
plot(Y_simu, type = 'l')


arms_mdl = ARMSmdl(Y_simu,ar = 2,k=2)
arms_mdl$coef

